        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t4-28.1-1"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "for conservative force stem:[bb(ii(F))], scalar additive quantity obeying\ncondition stem:[bb(ii(F)) = - bb(nabla) F], if it exists\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "For the definition of energy, see <<iso80000-5>>.\n\nA force is conservative when the force field is irrotational, i.e.\nstem:[bb(rot) bb(ii(F))=0], or stem:[bb(ii(F))] is perpendicular to the\nspeed of the body to ensure stem:[bb(ii(F)) * \"d\"r = 0].\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-J"
        },
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^2*s^(-2)"
        }
      ],
